import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['values'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Values')
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['width'], data['height'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Width')
    ax.set_ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between width and height?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_width = data['width'].mean()
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    
    plt.bar(['Average Width', 'Average Height'], [avg_width, avg_height], color=['blue', 'green'])
    plt.title('What is the average width and height of the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Average Width', 'Average Height'], loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['values'], vert=False)
    ax.set_yticklabels(['Values'])
    ax.set_title('What is the range of values in the dataset?')
    ax.axvline(data['values'].min(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['values'].min():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['values'].max(), color='g', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['values'].max():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='b', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['width'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['values'], label='Values')
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Values')
    plt.title('Are there any patterns or trends in the values over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
